    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-02-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-02-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="24"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.50/1–1749</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Assistant Secretary of State for Occupied
                        Areas</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Saltzman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the united States Representative on the Far
                        Eastern Commission</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McCoy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-02-08">February 8,
                            1949</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In accordance with previous oral instructions, and pursuant to the U.S. position
                    set forth in the final two paragraphs of your statement of December 9,
                        1948,<note n="1" xml:id="d24fn1">See <ref target="frus1948v06#pg_1056">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1948, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">vi</hi>, p. 1056</ref>.</note> regarding “Excessive
                    Concentration of Economic Power in Japan”, it is requested that the U.S.
                    Delegation oppose <gloss target="#t_C21">C 2</gloss>–230/4, “Policy on Excessive
                    Concentration of Economic Power”, and attempt to dissuade <gloss
                        target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss> Members from giving further consideration to
                    this or any other proposal which would have as its purpose the development of
                    additional policy on the subject of excessive concentration of economic power in
                    Japan. Should <gloss target="#t_C21">C 2</gloss>–230/4 or a similar proposal be
                    sent forward to the Commission, you should prevent its adoption by the
                    Commission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles</hi> E. <hi rend="smallcaps">Saltzman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
